Package: bvartools
Title: Functions for Bayesian Inference of Vector Autoregressive Models
Version: 0.0.2.9000
Date: 2019-02-27
Authors@R: person("Franz X.", "Mohr", email = "bvartools@outlook.com", role = c("aut","cre"))
Description: A collection of R and C++ functions, which assist in the set-up of algorithms for Bayesian inference of vector autoregressive (VAR) models. The functions are largely based on the introductory texts of Koop, G, & Korobilis, D. (2010) and Luetkepohl (2007). Computationally intensive functions are written in C++ using the 'RcppArmadillo' package of Eddelbuettel and Sanderson (2014).
License: GPL (>= 2)
Depends: R (>= 3.2.0)
Imports: coda, graphics, Rcpp (>= 0.12.14), stats
LinkingTo: Rcpp, RcppArmadillo
Encoding: UTF-8
RoxygenNote: 6.1.1
URL: https://github.com/franzmohr/bvartools
BugReports: https://github.com/franzmohr/bvartools/issues
Suggests: knitr, rmarkdown, stochvol
VignetteBuilder: knitr
